<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I hope everyone reads Xombie's post and tells everyone they know.  As an enchanter, this is a pet peeve of mine.  I get a buff cycle going and everyone gets buffs when I see them wearing off.  However, most of the pickup groups I've been in don't seem to understand this.<P>Almost without exception, the only time I get cleric buffs is when everyone buffs up the first time... or I ask.  Druids and shamans... same thing.  However, god forbid that insight or clarity should wear off anyone else!  Don't get me started on tanks... they seem to constantly whine when the least little buff wears off.  It's always a good time to ask the question... <P>"Want that celerity now, or should I keep these two extra Drolvargs that you pulled mezzed?"  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/wink.gif"><P>------------------<BR>The trick is to die but rarely (Travst).
</FONT>
