<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
When casting defensive or offensive spells during battle, always make sure you have the right target.  Click on their name in the group list or get used to which F-key (F1 is yourself - press again to get your pet, F2-F6 are your group mates) they're on.  Most often you'll find the same person(s) needs the same type of buff/heal/whatever.  <P>Unless you're an enchanter or other form for crowd controller, you should always use assist to ensure that you have the same target as the puller.  Set up a hotkey that does this:<P>/assist <pullername><BR>(Some also add another line that says /g Assisting <pullername>)<P>Why?  Because 3 mobs can do a lot of damage over a long period . . . all work on one, you'll pretty soon have two, then one . . .<P>If you're with an enchanter, ALWAYS use /assist on the puller, and make sure everyone in the group does as well.  There is no reason you should have to click on a target unless you're the puller or a crowd controller (enchanter mezzing, caster rooting, bard mezzing, etc.).<P>--------------------<P>Players on EverQuest:<BR>---------------------------<BR>[51 Reaver] Bhah (Ogre) <BR>There is 1 player in Twilight Zone.
</FONT>
