I comonly use the timing method to ensure that buffs are kept up, the only one I don't use would be AQ on myself.  No matter how long I have been doing this though I notice that people don't quite get it.<P>I was in a group in KC after I had gotten Boon of the Clear Mind.  For those who don't know, that is group clarity.  Boy did that spell make things easy.  Well I would see it start flashing and sit down, mem the spell and start casting.  Low and behold the Cleric I was with would ask, just when it started flashing, "Clarity please".  The first time I just ignored it and cast the spell, the next time I informed our cleric that it was not necessary to ask for it since it was a group buff and I could see it flashing, it continued this way for 4 hours.  <P>I guess some people just don't get it.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
  IP: <A HREF="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_ip&f=1&t=005983&reply_num=000013">Logged</A>
</FONT>
</td></tr>
</table>
</td></tr>


</table></td></tr></table>
</center>


